Owners' notes, some scribbled out, and other notes (f. 1r).

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Collection of works on Arabic grammar; copied in at least two hands.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī in brown ink; pointed.

binding.p: Disbound and probably never bound; held in paperboard folder.

origin.p: The copy is undated, possibly 18th century.

history.provenance: Gift of Solomon L. Skoss to the library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate adhered to paperboard wrapper).
Formerly owned by ʻAbd al-Ḥafīẓ ibn Muḥammad al-Ṣaghīr (note in ink, f. 1r).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate adhered to paperboard wrapper).
